main event: A civilian observer spotted multiple unidentified flying objects near DeFuniak Springs, Florida in 1966 and 1969.
interesting points: The objects were described as circular, metallic, and flying at very high speeds greater than 1,000 mph.
One of the objects made a sharp turn and rapidly descended towards the observer before sharply ascending and rejoining the other object.
The objects were not reflecting sunlight like normal aircraft and made no noise or visible exhaust.
Radar data from a nearby naval air station also detected the objects on multiple occasions.
The observer was a former airline pilot who believed the objects were military or secretly modified craft.
